<h2>Urban Cycle Parking Map </h2>
<p>In partnership with London Cycling Campaign, we are supporting a new cycle parking map.
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.urbancycleparking.org.uk/current/">Urban Cycle Parking</a> aims to capture current cycle parking locations and cyclists' views of where they would like to see more. </p>
<p>To make a cycle parking suggestion, or help map current locations, visit the <a href="http://www.urbancycleparking.org.uk">Urban Cycle Parking website</a>.</p>
<p>All suggested and current bike parking captured via the map is being regularly sent to us and the relevant highway authority for consideration. Thank you for your help.</p>
<h2>Finsbury Park Cycle Hub</h2>
<p>The new improved Finsbury Park Cycle Park is a 24-hour secure cycle parking facility that provides parking for 147 cycles.</p>
<p><strong>Located next to Finsbury Park Railway on Stroud Green Road, the facility provides:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Secure covered cycle parking for 147 cycles including trikes, cargo bikes, tandems and recumbents</li>
    <li>24-hour access, covered by CCTV</li>
    <li>Bike pump and repair stand</li>
    <li>Access Card facility</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://www.cyclehoop.rentals/cyclehub/fpcp">Apply online for membership</a> or call <strong>0208 699 1338</strong>.</p>
<h2>City of London cycle parking</h2>
<p>
The City of London provides free 24-hour cycle parking in staffed car parks at the following locations:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>London Wall</strong> - 176 spaces<br />
    Entry is between the Museum of London and Wood Street
    </li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Baynard House </strong>- 106 spaces<br />
    133 Queen Victoria Street, just north of Blackfriars Station
    </li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Tower Hill Car Park</strong> - 52 spaces<br />
    Entry is off Lower Thames Street
    </li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Minories </strong>- 15 spaces<br />
    Entry is off Mansell Street
    </li>
</ul>
<p><a href="/modes/cycling/cycling-in-london/avoid-theft">Read more about locking your bike safely</a>.
</p>
<h3>Heathrow cycle hub</h3>
<p>
The Heathrow cycle hub offers free cycle parking all around Heathrow, with more than 400 bicycle racks.
</p>
<p>A new cycle centre has opened at the airport and is the first of its kind anywhere in the UK, as well as being free to use.
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.heathrowairport.com/transport-and-directions/cycling-to-heathrow">Find out more about cycle parking at Heathrow</a>.</p>
